main event: A 10-year-old observer sighted a red and white blinking light in the sky that they believed was not a plane, as it disappeared to the east in a burst of speed.
interesting points: The observer could not definitively identify the object, and the sighting is being filed as 'insufficient data'.
The Air Force requested the observer fill out a detailed questionnaire to provide more information about the sighting.
The questionnaire includes detailed questions about the object's movement, color changes, brightness, and disappearance.
The observer provided a hand-drawn sketch of the object and its path, but no photograph was included.
The observer stated the object was self-luminous and much brighter than the surrounding sky or any other light source.
sighted object: a red and white blinking light in the sky
